
[1]trifling

   TRI'FLING, ppr. Acting or talking with levity, or without seriousness
   or being in earnest.

   1. a. Being of small value or importance; trivial; as a trifling debt;
   a trifling affair.

           TRI'FLING, n. Employment about things of no importance.
